    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Johnson</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 25, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Mr. Moran’s dispatch of the 4th of August, No.
                    88, concerning affairs in Brazil, is received, and his proceedings are
                    approved.</p>
                <p>I give you herewith a copy of an instruction for Mr. Webb, which goes by cable
                    to-day.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reverdy Johnson,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram per cable.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                            Johnson</persName>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Washington,</hi>
                            </placeName>
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-08-25">
                                <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 25, 1868.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Inform Webb at Rio that instructions to him were sent yesterday by United
                        States mail steamship from New York to Rio. His demand for permission for
                        the Wasp to go for Washburn is approved, but his demand for passport must be
                        suspended until further directions, which will go by the same mail steamer,
                        September 23d.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reverdy Johnson,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                                >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
